reviewText: C Lear example of how Hollywood can be great when they want...WJS
This is a great collection!!! Grace Kelly, Liz Taylor, Bette Davis, Joan Crawford, and Judy  Garland at their best,,,

I am a black and white movie FAN and adore the leading ladies included in this set.  The selection couldn't be better, an opportunity to weep, laugh, sing, cry tears of happiness, and cheer for a flawed but admirable heroine, each movie filled with superb actresses.  What an entertaining package  and delightful treat!

In "Now Voyager" Bette Davis plays a great heartbreaking role in a tragic romance with Paul Henried. "Mildred Pierce" has Joan Crawford wonderfully playing an independent woman after her divorce. "For Me and My Gal" has Judy Garland well cast in a romantic musical. "Father of the Bride" with Spencer Tracy and Joan Bennett is excellent romantic comedy. "Dial M for Murder" is a suspenseful murder mystery with Ray Milland and Grace Kelly.
